go_data.justification: CDC6 assembles at replication origins, forming pre-replicative complexes (pre-RCs) during the G1-phase of the cell cycle.
CDC6 is a component of the pre-replicative complex (pre-RC) that assembles at replication origins.
CDC6 is regulated by cell cycle- and cell growth-regulated proteolysis.
CDC6 is involved in DNA replication and is expected to be located in the nucleus.
